      "comment": "SANDI KINGDOM (1) has a fair record and proved too classy last time to win by 4 lengths at Richmond in a handy 18.65 beating Blurry. Has hit winning form and can measure up again. SMART MINX (8) turned in a plain performance last time when sixth at The Gardens over 400m behind Late In Arrival (23.36) in a Grade 5. The form out of last race has been strong. Should be about the money. TROPICAL ETHICS (2) showed little early speed at her last couple, the latest finishing sixth (20.15) in a Grade 5 at Bulli. Key runner who gets her chance to atone. RITZA KEVIE (3) deserves plenty of thought at his first run at this circuit.",
